name: Cornbread Chicken Pot Pie
author: Campbell's Kitchen
summary: You'll think back to simpler times when you serve this rich, cornbread-topped pot pie right in your own home.
ingredients: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  Campbell's® Condensed Cream of Chicken Soup (Regular or 98% Fat Free)
1 (8 ounce) can whole kernel corn, drained
2 cups cubed cooked chicken or turkey
directions: Heat the oven to 400 degrees F
Stir the soup, corn and chicken in a 9-inch pie plate
Stir the muffin mix, milk and egg in a small bowl just until blended
Spread the batter over the chicken mixture
Bake for 30 minutes or until the topping is golden brown
Let stand until the cheese is melted
